post_text: A heartfelt thanks to Rising Tide's Science Department from Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center in Boston. post_text:
Rising Tide Will Open a Second Enrollment Period for Grades 9, 10, and 11.

The principal enrollment period for the 2020-2021 school year has closed. The Annual Enrollment Lottery will be conducted in a public forum on Monday, February 10, 2020, at 9:00 am at 59 Armstrong Road in Plymouth, Massachusetts.

Rising Tide will open a Second Enrollment Period from Tuesday, February 11, 2020 through Wednesday March 11, 2020. For this Second Enrollment Period, Rising Tide will accept applications for grades 9, 10, and 11, as there is a possibility that the waiting lists for these grades, determined through the Annual Enrollment Lottery on Monday, will be exhausted at some point before February 15 of the upcoming school year. Rising Tide does not anticipate exhausting the waiting list for grades 5-8, determined through the Enrollment Lottery on Monday, and therefore is not able to accept applications for those grades in the Second Enrollment Period. On Friday, March 13, 2020, at 9:00 am, Rising Tide will conduct a Secondary Enrollment Lottery in a public forum at the school.

post_text:
Rising Tide has opened a Summer Enrollment Application Period for the 2019-2020 school year for grades 9, 10, and 11! Online applications can be filled out here - https://tinyurl.com/RTCPS-Application

The school currently has seats available for grades 9, 10, and 11 and is therefore accepting applications for those grades. Rising Tide currently has long waiting lists in grades 5-8 and does not anticipate exhausting the wait list for those grade levels and is therefore not able to accept applications for those grades.

Enrollment applications are due by Thursday, August 8, 2019 at 3 p.m. All applicants, including siblings of current students, must accurately submit the one-page application by the deadline to be eligible for enrollment. A public drawing will be held at 59 Armstrong Road for grades 9, 10, and 11 on Monday, August 12 at 10 a.m. if necessary.

Don't wait! Rising Tide's Spring Enrollment Lottery for 2019-2020 for grades 5, 9, 10, and 11 is ending on May 30th.

If interested in becoming a student, all applicants, including siblings of current students, must submit the online application - https://tinyurl.com/RTCPS-Application by the deadline to be eligible for enrollment. Paper copies of the application can also be picked up at the front desk in our school building located at 59 Armstrong Road in Plymouth. A public drawing will be held at at the school for grades 9, 10, and 11 on Monday, June 3 at 10:00 a.m.

Please note that this lottery period is only open to applicants enrolling for grade 5, 9, 10, or 11. Please contact the school at (508) 747-2620 ext. 506 with any questions.

post_text: Rising Tide addresses substance abuse and prevention in grades 5-12 throughout the school year and focuses on giving students the skills, knowledge and understanding of how substance abuse affects our community both locally and globally. Join us at the upcoming event, sponsored by the Plymouth Youth Development Collaborative, that complements our substance abuse lessons at Rising Tide. It's a great opportunity for parents to gain the knowledge for conversations with their children.
